</pre>

To check if further languages are supported visit https://www.torproject.org/dist/torbrowser/ or http://idnxcnkne4qt76tg.onion/dist/torbrowser/.

To make this language permanent when updating next time. Open {{Code|/etc/torbrowser.d//50_torbrowser_default}}.

<pre>
kdesudo kwrite /etc/torbrowser.d//50_torbrowser_default
</pre>

And add for example.

<pre>
TB_LANG="vi"
</pre>

Replace "vi" with "zh-CN" for Chinese and so on.

After setting this setting, [[Tor_Browser#Update_Tor_Browser|use the Tor Browser Updater]] to get a new version. Afterwards, you will have Tor Browser in your language.

=== Method 2 ===
'''Whonix-Workstation ONLY!'''

(1) Start Tor Browser.

(2) Find out which ESR Firefox version Tor Browser is using.

<pre>
Tor Browser -> Help -> About Tor Browser
</pre>

Should be something like ''10.0.11''.

(3) Install a language pack.

Go to [http://download-origin.cdn.mozilla.net/pub/mozilla.org/firefox/releases/10.0.11esr/linux-i686/xpi/ http://download-origin.cdn.mozilla.net/pub/mozilla.org/firefox/releases/'''10.0.11'''esr/linux-i686/xpi/]. You may need to change the '''bold''' part of that link depending on which ESR Firefox version Tor Browser is using!

(4) Restart Tor Browser.

(5) Done.

